# BDD Behavior-Driven Development Standards

## Core Principles

- **Given-When-Then** structure
- Describe in **business language**, not exposing implementation
- **Single responsibility** for each Scenario
- **Executable documentation** is the test

## Gherkin Syntax

### Feature File Structure

```gherkin
Feature: Order Free Shipping Calculation
  As an online shopping customer
  I want free shipping on orders over 100 yuan
  So that I can reduce shopping costs

  Scenario: Order amount exceeds 100 yuan, enjoy free shipping
    Given my shopping cart has items
      | Item Name | Unit Price | Quantity |
      | Laptop    | 5000       | 1        |
      | Wireless Mouse | 200    | 1        |
    When I click "Submit Order"
    Then shipping fee should be 0 yuan
    And system should show message "Order over 100 yuan, free shipping"

  Scenario: Order amount below 100 yuan, shipping fee charged
    Given my shopping cart total is 50 yuan
    When I click "Submit Order"
    Then shipping fee should be 10 yuan
    And system should show message "Order below 100 yuan, 10 yuan shipping fee"

  Scenario: Order exactly 100 yuan, enjoy free shipping
    Given my shopping cart total is 100 yuan
    When I click "Submit Order"
    Then shipping fee should be 0 yuan
```

### Keyword Definitions

| Keyword | Purpose | Repeatable |
|---------|---------|------------|
| Feature | Feature name | Once per file |
| Background | Shared preconditions for all Scenarios | Once per file |
| Scenario | Specific scenario | Multiple |
| Given | Precondition | Multiple |
| When | Trigger action | Once per Scenario |
| Then | Expected result | Multiple |
| And | Additional condition | Can be used with Given/When/Then |
| But | Additional condition | Same as And |
| Scenario Outline | Parameterized scenario | One, with multiple Examples |
| Examples | Parameter table | Once per Outline |

### Scenario Parameterization

```gherkin
Scenario Outline: Shipping fee calculation for different amounts
  Given my shopping cart total is <total> yuan
  When I click "Submit Order"
  Then shipping fee should be <shipping_fee> yuan

  Examples:
    | total | shipping_fee |
    | 0     | 10           |
    | 50    | 10           |
    | 99    | 10           |
    | 100   | 0            |
    | 150   | 0            |
    | 1000  | 0            |
```

### Data Tables

```gherkin
Scenario: Batch add items to shopping cart
  Given my shopping cart is empty
  When I add the following items:
    | Item ID | Item Name | Unit Price | Quantity |
    | P001    | Laptop    | 5000       | 1        |
    | P002    | Mouse     | 200        | 2        |
    | P003    | Keyboard  | 300        | 1        |
  Then shopping cart should have 3 items
  And shopping cart total should be 5700 yuan
```

## Scenario Writing Standards

### Good Naming

```gherkin
# ✅ Clearly express business value
Scenario: VIP member enjoys 10% discount
Scenario: Shipping fee is zero when order reaches free shipping threshold
Scenario: Order remains pending after payment failure

# ❌ Vague or exposing implementation
Scenario: Call calculateDiscount method
Scenario: Save method called after clicking save button
```

### Avoid Over-Detailing

```gherkin
# ✅ Focus on business results
Scenario: Automatically apply available discount at checkout
  Given shopping cart has items and has available coupon
  When checkout is completed
  Then discount amount should be deducted from total

# ❌ Over-detailed steps
Scenario: Automatically apply discount at checkout
  Given shopping cart has items
  When user clicks checkout button
  Then system calls discount service
  And discount service queries user coupons
  And returns discount information
  And system calculates discounted price
```

## Step Definitions

### Java Implementation

```java
public class OrderShippingSteps {

    private Order order;
    private Money shippingFee;

    @Given("my shopping cart total is {int} yuan")
    public void given_my_cart_total_is(int amount) {
        order = new Order(List.of(new OrderLine(product(), amount)));
    }

    @Given("my shopping cart has items")
    public void given_my_cart_has_items(DataTable dataTable) {
        List<OrderLine> lines = dataTable.asList().stream()
            .map(row -> new OrderLine(
                row.get("Item Name"),
                new Money(new BigDecimal(row.get("Unit Price")), Currency.USD),
                Integer.parseInt(row.get("Quantity"))
            ))
            .toList();
        order = new Order(lines);
    }

    @When("I click {string}")
    public void when_i_click(String button) {
        if (button.contains("Submit Order")) {
            shippingFee = order.calculateShippingFee();
        }
    }

    @Then("shipping fee should be {int} yuan")
    public void then_shipping_fee_should_be(int expected) {
        assertThat(shippingFee).isEqualTo(Money.of(expected));
    }

    @And("system should show message {string}")
    public void and_system_should_show_message(String message) {
        assertThat(order.getLastMessage()).isEqualTo(message);
    }
}
```

### TypeScript Implementation

```typescript
import { Given, When, Then, DataTable } from '@cucumber/cucumber';

let order: Order;
let shippingFee: Money;

Given('my shopping cart total is {int} yuan', async function (amount: number) {
  order = new Order([new OrderLine(product(), amount)]);
});

When('I click {string}', async function (button: string) {
  if (button.includes('Submit Order')) {
    shippingFee = order.calculateShippingFee();
  }
});

Then('shipping fee should be {int} yuan', async function (expected: number) {
  expect(shippingFee.value).toBe(expected);
});
```

## BDD and TDD Integration

```
BDD Acceptance Tests (What)
    ↓ Source of Requirements
TDD Unit Tests (How)
    ↓ Implementation
Code
```

### Mapping Relationship

| BDD Layer | TDD Layer | Purpose |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| Feature | Test Suite | Organize by feature |
| Scenario | Integration Test | End-to-end flow |
| Step | Unit Test | Specific behavior |

### Example

```gherkin
# BDD: Feature file
Feature: VIP Member Discount
  Scenario: VIP member enjoys 10% discount on purchase
    Given customer Zhang Wei is a VIP member
    And shopping cart total is 1000 yuan
    When checkout is completed
    Then actual payment amount should be 900 yuan
```

```java
// TDD: Unit tests
class VipDiscountTest {

    @Test
    void shouldApplyTenPercentDiscountForVipCustomers() {
        // Given
        Customer vipCustomer = Customer.createVip("Zhang Wei");
        Order order = new Order(List.of(new OrderLine(product(), Money.of(1000))));
        
        // When
        Money discount = discountService.calculate(order, vipCustomer);

        // Then
        assertThat(discount).isEqualTo(Money.of(100));
    }
}
```

## Scenario Review Checklist

### Business Value

- [ ] Scenario has clear business context
- [ ] Describes user/role
- [ ] Explains business value

### Completeness

- [ ] Covers positive flows
- [ ] Covers exception flows
- [ ] Covers boundary conditions

### Readability

- [ ] Uses business terminology
- [ ] No technical implementation details
- [ ] Given/When/Then structure is clear

### Executability

- [ ] Each Step can be automated
- [ ] No manual steps
- [ ] Data is explicit

## Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Symptoms | Correction |
|---------|----------|------------|
| Technical description | "Click button calls API" | "User logs into system" |
| Implementation leakage | "Input user ID to get user" | "Find user" |
| Too many steps | 10+ steps | Extract substeps |
| Vague assertion | "Order status correct" | "Order status should be paid" |
| Duplicate scenarios | Multiple Scenarios test same behavior | Merge or parameterize |
